com.github.tilastokeskus.matertis.core

Class GameGrid

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.tilastokeskus.matertis.core.GameGrid

  • public class GameGrid
extends Object
    Represents a game's grid. This class only holds data of stationary tetrominoes; that is, it doesn't take into account the currently falling tetromino in any way.
    Author:
    tilastokeskus
    See Also:
    Tetromino

    • Constructor Detail

      • GameGrid

        public GameGrid(int width,
        int height)
        Constructs a grid with the given width and height. Walls will be added around the grid, as well as an area on top of the game area.

        The true resulting width of the grid is: 

          width + 2
        This consists of the additional left and right wall.

        the height is: 

          height + 4 + 1
        This consists of the spawn area and the bottom wall.
        Parameters:
        width - width of the grid.
        height - height of the grid.

      • tetrominoCollides

        public boolean tetrominoCollides(Tetromino tetromino)
        Tells whether a tetromino is in collision with a non-empty cell in the provided matrix. An empty cell should be represented by zero (0).

        The matrix should be row-indiced. That is, grid[0] should return the first row in the matrix, and grid[3][6] should return the 7th cell of the 4th row, from top left to bottom right.

        Parameters:
        tetromino - a tetromino object whose collision should be tested against the grid.
        Returns:
        true if the tetromino collides with the grid, otherwise false.
        See Also:
        Tetromino

      • setTetromino

        public void setTetromino(Tetromino tetromino)
        Adds a tetromino's layout in the grid according to the tetromino's position.

        This method makes no checks of whether or not the tetromino collides with the grid, or if part of it is outside of the grid's bounds. If only a part of the tetromino is in the grid's bounds, the part that is in the grid's bounds will be added to the grid nonetheless.

        Parameters:
        tetromino - a tetromino object that should be added to the grid.
        See Also:
        Tetromino

      • handleFilledRows

        public int handleFilledRows()
        Searches for filled rows from the grid, top to bottom, and on each filled row it drops all rows on top of it by one.
        Returns:
        amount of filled rows found.
        See Also:
